portant%20part%20of%20our%20economy%2C%20no%20doubt%20about%20it.%20That%20hasn't%20changed%2C%26quot%3B%20Clare%20told%20reporters%20in%20Sydney%20after%20the%20announcement.%20%26quot%3BBut%20as%20students%20have%20come%20back%2C%20it%20has%20put%20pressure%20on%20the%20reputation%20of%20the%20sector.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EOverall%2C%20there%20will%20be%20about%2015%25%20more%20students%20allowed%20for%20universities%20and%2020%25%20fewer%20for%20vocational%20colleges%20in%202025%2C%20Clare%20said.%20The%20government%20was%20writing%20to%20individual%20universities%20to%20inform%20them%20of%20their%20caps%20on%20Tuesday.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BTo%20create%20the%20impression%20that%20this%20is%20somehow%20tearing%20down%20international%20education%20is%20absolutely%20and%20fundamentally%20wrong%2C%26quot%3B%20Clare%20said.%20%26quot%3BIt%20is%20about%20making%20sure%20that%20we%20set%20it%20up%20in%20a%20sustainable%20way%20for%20the%20future.%20We%20want%20students%20to%20come%20and%20study%20here.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EUniversities%20Australia%20Chair%20David%20Lloyd%20said%20the%20student%20caps%20would%20put%20a%20%26quot%3Bhandbrake%26quot%3B%20on%20the%20tertiary%20education%20sector.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EMigration%20controls%20should%20not%20be%20imposed%20%26quot%3Bat%20the%20expense%20of%20any%20one%20sector%2C%20particularly%20one%20as%20economically%20important%20as%20education%2C%26quot%3B%20Lloyd%20added%2C%20saying%20the%20limits%20would%20cause%20damage%20to%20Australia's%20research%20and%20development%20capacity.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20Independent%20Tertiary%20Education%20Council%20Australia%20said%20in%20a%20statement%20that%20universities%20needed%20more%20information%20about%20the%20changes%2C%20saying%20the%20announcement%20%26quot%3Bcreates%20more%20questions%20than%20answers.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAustralia%20is%20just%20the%20latest%20country%20to%20crack%20down%20on%20international%20students%20over%20migration%20concerns%2C%20with%20Canada%2C%20the%20Netherlands%20and%20the%20UK%20all%20implementing%20or%20considering%20measures%20targeting%20the%20university%20sector.%20In%20Australia%2C%20the%20government%20has%20been%20consulting%20for%20months%20over%20plans%20to%20impose%20limits%20on%20foreign%20students%2C%20part%20of%20a%20broader%20push%20to%20crack%20down%20on%20high%20post-Covid%20migration%20numbers.%20The%20surge%20in%20migration%20has%20coincided%20with%20rising%20voter%20concerns%20about%20a%20housing%20squeeze%20that%20sent%20rents%20soaring%2C%20proving%20politically%20damaging%20for%20the%20centre-left%20Labor%20government.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESupport%20for%20migration%20in%20Australia%20has%20fallen%20to%20its%20lowest%20level%20in%20five%20years%2C%20according%20to%20a%20poll%20released%20by%20Essential%20on%20Tuesday%2C%20with%2042%25%20of%20those%20surveyed%20saying%20it%20had%20a%20negative%20effect%20on%20the%20country.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EInternational%20students%20contributed%20%2448%20billion%20(%2432.5%20billion)%20to%20the%20Australian%20economy%20in%202023%2C%20making%20it%20the%20country's%20top%20services%20export.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20Property%20Council%20of%20Australia's%20Student%20Accommodation%20Council%20said%20the%20cap%20of%20270%2C000%20student%20visas%20was%20%26quot%3Bsustainable%26quot%3B%20and%20the%20government's%20announcement%20would%20give%20investors%20in%20student%20housing%20the%20confidence%20to%20keep%20putting%20money%20in%20the%20sector.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Ci%3E(Except%20for%20the%20headline%2C%20this%20story%20has%20not%20been%20edited%20by%20NDTV%20staff%20and%20is%20published%20from%20a%20syndicated%20feed.)%3C%2Fi%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1724737200000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fc.ndtvimg.com%2F2024-08%2Ffbqec90g_australia-students-generic-bloomberg-_625x300_27_August_24.jpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Fworld-news%2Faustralia-to-limit-foreign-students