est%20coast%20guard%20fleet%2C%20and%20it's%20still%20building%20up%20on%20an%20ambitious%20scale.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EIt's%20been%20taking%20ships%20from%20its%20navy%20and%20could%20be%20getting%20its%20own%20vessel%20modeled%20after%20a%20destroyer.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EExperts%20say%20the%20acquisitions%20mean%20it's%20moving%20closer%20to%20being%20a%20naval%20reserve%20or%20auxiliary%20force.%3C%2Fli%3E%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20May%2C%20military%20experts%20spied%20a%20peculiar%2C%20half-built%20vessel%20sitting%20among%20warships%20at%20a%20Shanghai%20dockyard.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESatellite%20images%20showed%20it%20had%20the%20shape%20and%20size%20of%20a%20Type-052D%2C%20an%20advanced%20guided-missile%20destroyer%20in%20China's%20navy.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20this%20ship%20was%20missing%20key%20features%2C%20such%20as%20a%20vertical%20launch%20system%20for%20missiles%20and%20its%20%26quot%3BDragon's%20Eye%26quot%3B%20radar%2C%20a%20standard%20system%20for%20Chinese%20warships.%20Its%20main%20gun%20was%20also%20smaller%20than%20usual.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOne%20detail%20stood%20out%20above%20all%3A%20the%20paint%20job.%20Chinese%20navy%20ships%20are%20gray%2C%20and%20this%20apparent%20Type-052D%20came%20in%20white%20%E2%80%94%20the%20mark%20of%20a%20coast%20guard%20vessel.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20discovery%20led%20to%20speculation%2C%20which%20has%20since%20been%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.scmp.com%2Fnews%2Fchina%2Fmilitary%2Farticle%2F3274494%2Fchinese-coastguard-set-get-new-ship-modelled-advanced-type-052d-destroyer%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ebacked%20up%20by%20local%20reports%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20that%20China's%20coast%20guard%2C%20a%20law%20enforcement%20agency%2C%20was%20obtaining%20a%20ship%20modeled%20after%20a%206%2C500-ton%20naval%20destroyer.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20vessel%20is%20just%20one%20of%20several%20big-ticket%20acquisitions%20believed%20to%20be%20destined%20for%20the%20maritime%20force%2C%20which%20is%20now%20at%20a%20stage%20where%20its%20capabilities%20likely%20carry%20serious%20implications%20if%20Beijing%20goes%20to%20war%20with%20another%20naval%20power.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20policing%20body%2C%20moved%20in%202018%20to%20fall%20under%20military%20command%2C%20is%20undergoing%20one%20of%20the%20world's%20most%20aggressive%20expansions%20at%20a%20time%20when%20the%20Chinese%20coast%20guard%20is%20increasingly%20becoming%20the%20center%20of%20tensions%20with%20its%20neighbors.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20sheer%20size%20and%20strength%20of%20its%20fleet%2C%20estimated%20at%20250%20vessels%20of%20at%20least%20500%20tons%20each%2C%20has%20led%20to%20Western%20experts%20often%20calling%20it%20a%20%26quot%3Bsecond%20navy.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAnd%20it's%20continued%20to%20break%20ground%20with%20bigger%20and%20bolder%20ships.%20Earlier%20this%20month%2C%20a%20state-run%20shipbuilding%20institute%20announced%20it%20was%20preparing%20an%20unspecified%20%26quot%3Bmothership%26quot%3B%20for%20the%20high%20seas%2C%20leading%20to%20rumors%20that%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fchina-mothership-coast-guard-drone-aircraft-carrier-south-sea-2024-8%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ecoast%20guard%20was%20due%20to%20receive%20a%20seafaring%20drone%20carrier.%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20July%2C%20China%20anchored%20one%20of%20its%20two%20%26quot%3BMonster%26quot%3B%20ships%20%E2%80%94%20the%20world's%20largest-ever%20coast%20guard%20vessels%20displacing%2012%2C000%20tons%20each%20%E2%80%94%20in%20the%20Philippines'%20exclusive%20economic%20zone.%20It%20was%20an%20incredible%20show%20of%20power%2C%20which%20Manila%20accused%20of%20being%20an%20intimidation%20tactic.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%221600%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22The%20Chinese%20coast%20guard%20vessel%20nicknamed%20the%20%26quot%3BMonster%26quot%3B%20rests%20on%20Philippine%20waters.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F66c854b243b5e59d16b48d94%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221200%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EThe%20Philippines%20published%20photos%20of%20China%20anchoring%20the%20world's%20biggest%20coast%20guard%20vessel%20in%20its%20waters.%3Cp%3EPhilippine%20Coast%20Guard%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EExperts%20think%20Beijing's%20ambitions%20for%20the%20agency%20are%20global.%20China%20has%20made%20it%20no%20secret%20that%20it%20intends%20to%20expand%20its%20maritime%20strength%20for%20distant%20operations%2C%20establishing%20a%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcarnegieendowment.org%2Fposts%2F2019%2F05%2Fthe-pla-navys-strategic-transformation-to-the-far-seas-how-far-how-threatening-and-whats-to-be-done%3Flang%3Den%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%26quot%3Bfar-seas%20protection%26quot%3B%20doctrine%3C%2Fa%3E%20in%202015.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIts%20coast%20guard%20looks%20poised%20to%20play%20a%20significant%20role%2C%20John%20Michael%20Dahm%2C%20a%20former%20US%20Navy%20intelligence%20officer%20and%20a%20senior%20fellow%20at%20the%20Mitchell%20Institute%20for%20Aerospace%20Studies%2C%20told%20Business%20Insider.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThat%20the%20Chinese%20coast%20guard%20would%20use%20these%20new%2C%20larger%20ships%20and%20capabilities%20to%20establish%20a%20security%20presence%20farther%20from%20China%20probably%20has%20the%20largest%20security%20implications%20for%20the%20US%20and%20its%20allies%2C%26quot%3B%20Dahm%20said.%20%26quot%3BNot%20just%20in%20Asia%2C%20but%20around%20the%20world.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%229114ae90-a9d2-47b8-b25c-dd9693d3c8eb%5C%22%3EWhy%20a%20destroyer%3F%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EChina's%20coast%20guard%20expansion%20isn't%20happening%20in%20isolation.%20It's%20locked%20in%20a%20pseudo-arms%20race%20with%20its%20neighbors%20in%20the%20resource-rich%20East%20and%20South%20China%20Seas%2C%20chiefly%20Japan%20and%20the%20Philippines.%20Both%20are%20US%20allies.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBeijing%20has%2C%20for%20decades%2C%20already%20been%20beefing%20up%20its%20coast%20guard%20with%20dozens%20of%20former%20People's%20Liberation%20Army%20Navy%20ships%2C%20including%20corvettes%20that%20were%20decommissioned%20and%20modified%20to%20remove%20heavy%20weaponry.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20its%20rivals%20have%20recently%20started%20working%20more%20closely%20as%20tensions%20mount%20over%20regional%20disputes%2C%20most%20of%20which%20China%20has%20been%20accused%20of%20initiating.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EManila%20is%20upgrading%20its%20coast%20guard%20with%20five%20Japan-made%20ships%20worth%20a%20total%20of%20%24400%20million%2C%20while%20Tokyo%20is%20planning%20a%20giant%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthediplomat.com%2F2024%2F07%2Fjapan-to-build-major-new-vessel-for-the-senkaku-islands%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E30%2C000-ton%20vessel%3C%2Fa%3E%20for%20its%20respectable%20150-ship%20policing%20fleet.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BSize%20does%20matter%2C%26quot%3B%20Dahm%20said.%20%26quot%3BA%20vessel's%20size%20and%20displacement%20often%20translate%20directly%20into%20capabilities.%20A%20bigger%20ship%20means%20more%20people%2C%20more%20weapons%2C%20more%20fuel%2C%20more%20endurance%2C%20more%20range.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWestern%20experts%20think%20the%20destroyer-esque%20ship%20being%20assembled%20in%20Shanghai%20is%20part%20of%20China's%20effort%20to%20stay%20ahead.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BChina%20is%20upping%20the%20ante%20again%20by%20bringing%20in%20the%20most%20kind%20of%20modern%2C%20advanced%20form%20of%20a%20coast%20guard%20ship%2C%26quot%3B%20said%20Vina%20Nadjibulla%2C%20vice%20president%20of%20research%20and%20strategy%20at%20the%20Asia%20Pacific%20Foundation%20of%20Canada.%20%26quot%3BWe%20should%20see%20it%20more%20as%20a%20naval%20ship%20than%20a%20coast%20guard%20ship.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%224908%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22The%20type%20052D%20guided%20missile%20destroyer%20Guiyang%20of%20the%20Chinese%20People's%20Liberation%20Army%20%20Navy%20participates%20in%20a%20naval%20parade%20to%20commemorate%20the%2070th%20anniversary%20of%20the%20founding%20of%20China's%20PLA%20Navy%20in%20the%20sea%20near%20Qingdao%2C%20in%20eastern%20China's%20Shandong%20province%20in%20April%202019.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F66c8531d1aa2ac29ee339201%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%223272%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EThe%20Type-052D%20guided%20missile%20destroyer%20is%20one%20of%20China's%20most%20advanced%20warships.%3Cp%3EMARK%20SCHIEFELBEIN%2FAFP%20via%20Getty%20Images%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EFrom%20China's%20perspective%2C%20a%20destroyer-sized%20ship%20would%20fill%20a%20gap%20in%20its%20fleet%2C%20said%20Collin%20Koh%2C%20a%20senior%20fellow%20at%20the%20Institute%20of%20Defence%20and%20Strategic%20Studies%20at%20Singapore's%20Nanyang%20Technological%20University.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20coast%20guard's%20regular%20fleet%20goes%20up%20to%204%2C000%20tons%2C%20before%20a%20dramatic%20leap%20to%20its%2012%2C000-ton%20%26quot%3BMonster%26quot%3B%20ships.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EKoh%20said%20China's%20%26quot%3BMonster%26quot%3B%20ship%20may%20have%20been%20staring%20down%20the%20Philippines%20in%20the%20South%20China%20Sea%2C%20but%20it's%20impractical%20to%20station%20such%20vessels%20so%20far%20away%20for%20extended%20periods.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIt's%20expensive%20to%20operate%20and%20deploy%20this%20sort%20of%20ship%2C%20because%20it's%20too%20big%20and%20it's%20not%20suited%20for%20this%20purpose%2C%26quot%3B%20Koh%20said.%20%26quot%3BIt's%20meant%20more%20as%20a%20command%20ship%20and%20a%20disaster%20relief%20platform%20than%20to%20go%20out%20there%20and%20show%20force.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EA%20ship%20modeled%20after%20the%20Type-052D%20destroyer%2C%20at%206%2C500%20tons%2C%20could%20fill%20that%20power-projecting%20purpose%2C%20especially%20if%20produced%20in%20greater%20numbers%2C%20Koh%20added.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EQuestions%20also%20remain%20as%20to%20what%20sort%20of%20vessel%20China%20is%20planning%20for%20its%20teased%20coast%20guard%20%26quot%3Bmothership.%26quot%3B%20Local%20pundits%20have%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fchina-mothership-coast-guard-drone-aircraft-carrier-south-sea-2024-8%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eguessed%20it%20may%20be%20a%20drone%20carrier%20or%20even%20an%20aircraft%20carrier%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20though%20the%20latter%20is%20unlikely.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20build-up%20seems%20a%20world%20away%20from%20what's%20traditionally%20been%20understood%20as%20the%20coast%20guard's%20role%3A%20to%20police%20fishermen%20and%20deter%20smugglers.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EJapan's%20coast%20guard%20already%20has%20five%206%2C500-ton%20patrol%20ships%2C%20and%20if%20China%20expands%20its%20own%20agency%20with%20vessels%20of%20that%20class%2C%20the%20region%20is%20set%20to%20be%20filled%20by%20warship-sized%20boats%20jockeying%20for%20dominance.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EFor%20comparison%2C%20the%20US%20Coast%20Guard's%20largest%20cutters%20are%20the%20size%20of%20frigates%2C%20at%20about%204%2C500%20tons.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BAnything%20the%20China%20coast%20guard%20does%20might%20be%20considered%20unprecedented%20at%20this%20point%2C%26quot%3B%20said%20Dahm%20of%20the%20Mitchell%20Institute.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%223c5b5737-5ed3-4a3f-aeed-69b3fd84f11e%5C%22%3EA%20coast%20guard%20that%20can%20go%20to%20war%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EOne%20of%20the%20most%20significant%20developments%20of%20a%20burgeoning%20Chinese%20coast%20guard%20is%20that%20its%20ships%20might%20make%20a%20difference%20in%20a%20war.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20US%20Navy%20far%20outstrips%20Beijing's%20in%20raw%20tonnage%20and%20firepower%2C%20but%20it%20is%20losing%20out%20in%20the%20numbers%20game%2C%20with%20roughly%20300%20vessels%20to%20the%20Chinese%20navy's%20370.%20Add%20a%20sizable%20coast%20guard%20force%2C%20and%20China%20stands%20to%20far%20exceed%20Washington's%20count.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThey're%20using%20quite%20common%20baseline%20hulls%20as%20existing%20PLAN%20vessels%2C%26quot%3B%20said%20Koh.%20%26quot%3BAnd%20that%20gives%20us%20the%20impression%20that%20they're%20maintaining%20some%20level%20of%20platform%20commonality.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThat's%20important%2C%20because%20a%20common%20platform%20leaves%20open%20the%20possibility%20of%20adding%20naval%20weapons%20to%20coast%20guard%20ships.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BA%20coast%20guard%20Type-052D%20might%20have%20no%20vertical%20launch%20system%20on%20board%2C%20but%20it%20still%20has%20enough%20deck%20space%20to%20mount%20weapons%2C%26quot%3B%20said%20Koh.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20navy%20corvettes%20obtained%20by%20the%20coast%20guard%2C%20for%20example%2C%20might%20possibly%20be%20refitted%20with%20their%20old%20weapons.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIf%20they%20can%20remove%20some%20systems%2C%20it%20means%20they%20can%20be%20reinstalled%20in%20times%20of%20conflict%2C%26quot%3B%20Koh%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%224000%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22The%20Type%20056%20patrol%20vessel%20of%20the%20Chinese%20Coast%20Guard%20in%20Zhifu%20Bay%2C%20Yantai%2C%20East%20China's%20Shandong%20province%2C%20Jan%209%2C%202023.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F66c8569643b5e59d16b48de8%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%222667%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EMore%20than%2020%20Chinese%20Type-056%20navy%20corvettes%20have%20been%20repurposed%20without%20their%20anti-ship%20missiles%20to%20become%20coast%20guard%20vessels.%3Cp%3ETANG%20KE%2FFeature%20China%2FFuture%20Publishing%20via%20Getty%20Images%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EBenjamin%20Blandin%2C%20a%20researcher%20and%20network%20coordinator%20at%20the%20Yokosuka%20Council%20on%20Asia-Pacific%20Studies%2C%20told%20BI%20that%20he's%20noticed%20the%20Chinese%20coast%20guard%20also%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.scmp.com%2Fnews%2Fchina%2Fdiplomacy%2Farticle%2F3268460%2Fchina-coast-guard-what-does-it-do-and-how-did-it-become-so-powerful%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Erecently%20acquired%20landing%20craft.%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThat's%20quite%20bizarre%20to%20me.%20I%20don't%20know%20why%20a%20coast%20guard%20would%20ever%20need%20landing%20capacities%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ELegally%2C%20little%20stands%20in%20the%20way%20of%20China%20using%20its%20coast%20guard%20in%20open%20conflict.%20The%20agency%20falls%20under%20the%20People's%20Armed%20Police%2C%20which%20reports%20to%20central%20military%20leadership.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ECoast%20guard%20laws%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22http%3A%2F%2Fwww.mod.gov.cn%2Fgfbw%2Ffgwx%2Fflfg%2F4877678.html%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ewere%20also%20changed%20in%202021%20%3C%2Fa%3Eto%20allow%20the%20use%20of%20force%20when%20China's%20%26quot%3Bsovereign%20rights%20and%20jurisdiction%20are%20infringed%20upon.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BClearly%2C%20they%20are%20being%20treated%20by%20the%20Chinese%20authorities%20as%20a%20navy%20reserve%20or%20a%20navy%20auxiliary%2C%26quot%3B%20Blandin%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EChina's%20foreign%20ministry%20press%20center%20did%20not%20respond%20to%20a%20request%20for%20comment%20sent%20by%20BI.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%226b7c5a4b-0117-435a-803e-8d9b8d7e6228%5C%22%3EAmbitions%20for%20a%20global%20policing%20force%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EA%20key%20element%20in%20China's%20announcement%20for%20its%20coast%20guard%20%26quot%3Bmothership%26quot%3B%20was%20the%20phrase%20%26quot%3Bfar%20seas.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAlmost%20nothing%20has%20been%20revealed%20about%20the%20new%20ship%2C%20but%20Chinese%20shipbuilders%20said%20it's%20designed%20to%20provide%20%26quot%3Bcomprehensive%20support%26quot%3B%20on%20long-range%20missions.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThat's%20a%20clue%20that%20China%20might%20intend%20to%20send%20its%20coast%20guard%20on%20missions%20far%20beyond%20the%20East%20and%20South%20China%20Seas%2C%20Dahm%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BFor%20example%2C%20in%20the%20not-t