20the%20US%20Congress%2C%20Facebook%20CEO%20Mark%20Zuckerberg%20has%20alleged%20that%20the%20US%20government%20under%20Joe%20Biden%20%26quot%3Brepeatedly%20pressured%26quot%3B%20Meta%20to%20censor%20certain%20content%20on%20its%20platforms.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20the%20letter%20addressed%20to%20US%20House%20of%20Representatives%2C%20Mr%20Zuckerberg%20said%20that%20the%20platform%20had%20to%20make%20some%20changes%2C%20that%20%26quot%3Bwith%20the%20benefit%20of%20hindsight%20and%20new%20information%2C%26quot%3B%20they%20won't%20make%20today.%20He%20added%20that%20he%20regrets%20not%20being%20%26quot%3Bmore%20outspoken%26quot%3B%20about%20it.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIn%202021%2C%20senior%20officials%20from%20the%20Biden%20Administration%2C%20including%20the%20White%20House%2C%20repeatedly%20pressured%20our%20teams%20for%20months%20to%20censor%20certain%20COVID-19%20content%2C%20including%20humor%20and%20satire%2C%20and%20expressed%20a%20lot%20of%20frustration%20with%20our%20teams%20when%20we%20didn't%20agree.%20Ultimately%2C%20it%20was%20our%20decision%20whether%20or%20not%20to%20take%20content%20down%2C%20and%20we%20own%20our%20decisions%2C%20including%20COVID-19-related%20changes%20we%20made%20to%20our%20enforcement%20in%20the%20wake%20of%20this%20pressure.%20I%20believe%20the%20government%20pressure%20was%20wrong%2C%20and%20I%20regret%20that%20we%20were%20not%20more%20outspoken%20about%20it%2C%26quot%3B%20the%20letter%20read.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EZuckerberg%20said%20he%20felt%20that%20Meta%20should%20not%20compromise%20its%20content%20standards%20due%20to%20pressure%20from%20any%20Administration.%20%26quot%3BWe're%20ready%20to%20push%20back%20if%20something%20like%20this%20happens%20again%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20Meta%20CEO%20also%20spoke%20of%20a%20FBI%20warning%20about%20a%20%26quot%3Bpotential%20Russian%20disinformation%20operation%20about%20the%20Biden%20family%20and%20Burisma%20in%20the%20lead%20up%20to%20the%202020%20election.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThat%20fall%2C%20when%20we%20saw%20a%20New%20York%20Post%20story%20reporting%20on%20corruption%20allegations%20involving%20then-Democratic%20presidential%20nominee%20Joe%20Biden's%20family%2C%20we%20sent%20that%20story%20to%20fact-checkers%20for%20review%20and%20temporarily%20demoted%20it%20while%20waiting%20for%20a%20reply.%20It's%20since%20been%20made%20clear%20that%20the%20reporting%20was%20not%20Russian%20disinformation%2C%20and%20in%20retrospect%2C%20we%20shouldn't%20have%20demoted%20the%20story.%20We've%20changed%20our%20policies%20and%20processes%20to%20make%20sure%20this%20doesn't%20happen%20again%20for%20instance%2C%20we%20no%20longer%20temporarily%20demote%20things%20in%20the%20US%20while%20waiting%20for%20fact-checkers%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EMr%20Zuckerberg%20reiterated%20his%20support%20for%20the%20electoral%20infrastructure%20ahead%20of%20the%20presidential%20elections%20in%20November.%20He%20spoke%20of%20he%20made%20to%20strengthen%20the%20infrastructure%20in%20a%20non-partisan%20way.%20%26quot%3BI%20know%20that%20some%20people%20believe%20this%20work%20benefited%20one%20party%20over%20the%20other.%20My%20goal%20is%20to%20be%20neutral%20and%20not%20play%20a%20role%20one%20way%20or%20another%20or%20to%20even%20appear%20to%20be%20playing%20a%20role.%20So%20I%20don't%20plan%20on%20making%20a%20similar%20contribution%20this%20cycle%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1724728860000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fc.ndtvimg.com%2F2024-02%2Fcmktlo9s_zuckerberg-us-senate-afp_625x300_01_February_24.jpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Fworld-news%2Fbiden-administration-repeatedly-pressured-meta-mark-zuckerberg-in-letter-6426079%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22In%20a%20letter%20to%20the%20US%20Congress%2C%20Facebook%20CEO%20Mark%20Zuckerberg%20has%20alleged%20that%20the%20US%20government%20under%20Joe%20Biden%20%26quot%3Brepeatedly%20pressured%26quot%3B%20Meta%