e%20of%20the%20main%20things%20that's%20critical%20with%20heat%20stroke%20is%20you%20start%20to%20see%20cognitive%20impairment%2C%26quot%3B%20said%20Lacy%20Alexander%2C%20a%20kinesiology%20professor%20at%20Penn%20State%20University%20who%20wasn't%20involved%20in%20treating%20Steel.%20The%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fweather-in-summer-heat-impact-on-health-2018-7%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ebrain%20is%20sensitive%3C%2Fa%3E%20to%20high%20temperatures.%20When%20it%20gets%20too%20hot%2C%20%26quot%3Byou%20start%20to%20get%20that%20cooking%20of%20brain%20and%20neural%20tissue%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%229ea47a1e-4dd8-4784-b759-b9d084990d12%5C%22%3EThe%20long-term%20effects%20of%20heat%20stroke%20can%20be%20debilitating%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%221000%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Amy%20Steel%20feeds%20a%20baby%20kangroo%20from%20a%20bottle%20in%20a%20bag%20around%20her%20neck%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F66ccca151aa2ac29ee34606d%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22876%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EEight%20years%20after%20getting%20heat%20stroke%2C%20Amy%20Steel%20is%20still%20dealing%20with%20its%20effects.%3Cp%3ELewis%20Blaustein%2FEcoAthletes%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EAlexander%20said%20restricted%20blood%20flow%20to%20the%20gut%20during%20heat%20stroke%20can%20release%20bacteria%20into%20the%20bloodstream.%20This%20can%20cause%20a%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fcytokine-storm-severe-coronavirus-case-death-2020-5%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ecytokine%20storm%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20similar%20to%20the%20way%20some%20people's%20immune%20systems%20overreact%20to%20COVID-19.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BYou%20see%20this%20really%20huge%20response%20of%20the%20immune%20system%20to%20severe%20heat-related%20events%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20said.%20This%20kind%20of%20overreaction%20can%20trigger%20a%20s